  "event_preview": "Dover Motor Speedway is a 1.0-mile (1.609 km) concrete oval in Dover, Delaware, with 24-degree banking in the turns and 9-degree banking on the straights. The BetRivers 200 is the fourteenth race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season, run over 200 laps (200 miles) with stage breaks at laps 45 and 90. With 39 entries for 38 available positions, one team will fail to qualify — Connor Zilisch, who won last weekend at Watkins Glen, does not return this week, with Carson Kvapil taking over the No. 1 JR Motorsports Chevrolet in his place.\n\nJustin Allgaier leads the championship standings and enters Dover with one of the strongest track records in the field. Cup Series regular Ross Chastain pulls double duty in the No. 9 JR Motorsports Chevrolet — his fifth O'Reilly start of 2026 and second in that car, having finished 14th at Darlington in March. Austin Hill, Sam Mayer and defending series champion Jesse Love are also among the strongest contenders.\n\nThe all-time O'Reilly Series qualifying lap record at Dover belongs to Erik Jones, who posted a 22.739-second lap (158.318 mph) in October 2016. The race speed record belongs to Joey Logano, who averaged 131.219 mph during his victory in September 2013.",
